{
  "local_port": 41122,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is the procedure to check your PF balance?",
  "response": "To check your Provident Fund (PF) balance, you can follow these steps depending on the method you prefer:\n\n### 1. **Using the EPFO Website:**\n   - **Step 1:** Visit the official EPFO website: [epfindia.gov.in](http://epfindia.gov.in).\n   - **Step 2:** Navigate to the \"Our Services\" section and select \"For Members.\"\n   - **Step 3:** Click on \"Balance/Passbook.\"\n   - **Step 4:** Enter your Universal Account Number (UAN), password, and captcha code.\n   - **Step 5:** Click on \"Login,\" and you will be able to view your PF balance.\n\n### 2. **Using the EPFO Mobile App:**\n   - **Step 1:** Download the EPFO app from the Google Play Store or Apple App Store.\n   - **Step 2:** Register using your mobile number linked with your UAN.\n   - **Step 3:** Once registered, log in and navigate to the \u201cEmployee Centric Services\u201d section.\n   - **Step 4:** Click on \u201cView Balance\u201d to check your current PF balance.\n\n### 3. **Sending an SMS:**\n   - You can also check your PF balance via SMS. Typically, you can send a message in the format:\n     ```\n     EPFOHO UAN <Language Code>\n     ```\n   - Replace `<Language Code>` with the code for your preferred language (e.g., Hindi = HIN, English = ENG). \n   - Your UAN number must be registered with your EPF account.\n\n### 4. **Missed Call Service:**\n   - You can give a missed call to 011-22901406 from your registered mobile number.\n   - After a brief moment, you will receive an SMS with details of your PF balance.\n\n### 5. **Through Employer:**\n   - You can also check your balance through your employer's payroll department. They may provide you with the necessary information regarding your PF account.\n\n### **Note:**\n- Ensure your UAN is activated and linked to your Aadhaar and bank account for these services to work effectively.\n- You may need to create a password for the online methods if you haven\u2019t done so already.\n\nChoose the method that works best for you based on your convenience!",
